The drivers of two powerboats which crashed and flipped mid air during a qualifying session miraculously escaped uninjured.

Spectators looked on in horror as the two vessels collided at the end of a 120mph straight at the F2 World Powerboat Championships in Nottinghamshire.

The No 14 boat piloted by Swedish driver Jonas Andersson launched into the air and flipped 360 degrees before crashing back into the water.

