Meanwhile the No 6 racer driven by fellow Swede Ola Petterssen barrel-rolled before landing upright.

It is believed that neither competitor suffered serious injury in the crash at the National Water Sports Centre at Holme Pierrepont, Nottinghamshire on Saturday.

Neither driver qualified for the main Grand Prix race yesterday.

Photographer Graham Jones, who captured the dramatic shots, said the boats suddenly 'took off'.

'They had just come down the straight and were about to turn around the bouys at the end of the circuit when they clipped each other,' he said.

